00:53.870 --> 00:55.470
âª

01:01.344 --> 01:03.245
âª

01:04.513 --> 01:06.614
(Spartan grunts and pants)

01:07.550 --> 01:11.152
<i>Mallory:</i> <i>Amy, what're
you doing</i> <i>out here?</i>

01:11.219 --> 01:13.888
Amy: I'm trying to work with
Spartan in a quiet place.

01:13.956 --> 01:15.156
I'm not talking
about Spartan!

01:15.223 --> 01:16.624
I'm talking about Ty
moving out

01:16.692 --> 01:18.893
and you acting like everything
is all good!

01:18.961 --> 01:21.495
It's just a couple of miles
up the road, Mallory.

01:21.563 --> 01:24.030
And, besides, we both agreed
that this was the best thing.

01:24.098 --> 01:25.866
Yeah. If you love someone,
set them free.

01:25.934 --> 01:27.901
Then just sit there
and watch

01:27.969 --> 01:29.870
as he takes off
and keeps going

01:29.938 --> 01:31.572
and going and going...

01:31.639 --> 01:33.674
Mallory,
it's not like that.

01:33.741 --> 01:35.108
I mean,
we're not kids anymore.

01:35.176 --> 01:37.410
We know how we feel
and we trust each other.

01:37.478 --> 01:39.278
Hey, where're you going?

01:39.346 --> 01:41.246
Grrr!
Thank you!

01:43.884 --> 01:45.184
(Spartan whinnies)

01:45.251 --> 01:46.652
<i>Jack:</i>
<i>So, you heard from Miranda</i>

01:46.720 --> 01:48.921
since Shane went back
to Moose Jaw?

01:48.989 --> 01:51.724
Well, she called to say
that they arrived.

01:51.792 --> 01:53.058
Since then, nothing.

01:53.126 --> 01:54.693
<i>Jack:</i>
<i>So, what? That's it?</i>

01:54.760 --> 01:57.395
From now on, I have to keep
lying to my granddaughters

01:57.463 --> 01:58.463
to protect you?

01:58.531 --> 02:00.131
I wouldn't call it lying,
Jack.

02:00.199 --> 02:03.502
I mean, I'd call it...
Not telling the truth.

02:03.569 --> 02:05.069
Yeah. Well, you'd call
a spade a diamond

02:05.137 --> 02:06.070
if it wins you the hand.

02:06.138 --> 02:07.606
This can't go on, Tim.

02:07.673 --> 02:09.240
I'm getting sick and tired
of pussy-footing around

02:09.308 --> 02:10.975
this whole issue.

02:11.042 --> 02:12.209
Well, I'm trying,
Jack.

02:12.276 --> 02:13.343
(Phone rings)

02:15.747 --> 02:17.280
Just... here,
hang on a second.

02:17.348 --> 02:19.583
I gotta take this.

02:19.651 --> 02:21.685
<i>Oh, surprise, surprise...</i>

02:21.753 --> 02:23.554
<i>No, I'm not busy.</i>
<i>I'm...</i>

02:23.622 --> 02:25.288
<i>Well, helping Jack.</i>

02:25.356 --> 02:26.556
Okay, yeah.

02:27.491 --> 02:28.558
Bye.

02:30.528 --> 02:32.328
What was that all about?

02:32.396 --> 02:34.096
Uh...
Oh, that was the track.

02:34.164 --> 02:34.864
I gotta go.

02:34.932 --> 02:35.798
The track?

02:35.866 --> 02:36.799
It's important, Jack,

02:36.867 --> 02:38.034
I gotta do this
right now.

02:38.101 --> 02:39.035
So?

02:39.102 --> 02:40.136
So?

02:40.203 --> 02:41.537
Miranda? Shane?

02:41.604 --> 02:42.704
Yeah, yeah.

02:44.641 --> 02:46.041
I'm-I'm on it.

02:47.276 --> 02:49.277
(Truck door closes
and starts up)

02:56.619 --> 02:57.685
(Objects clatter)

03:00.956 --> 03:04.191
You're not gonna forget this,
are you?

03:08.096 --> 03:09.830
Of course not.

03:11.667 --> 03:13.300
Still fits.

03:13.368 --> 03:15.401
You need to tilt it down
a little.

03:15.469 --> 03:16.570
- How's that?
- Better.

03:16.637 --> 03:18.171
Yeah?

03:18.238 --> 03:19.305
You know,
I used to think

03:19.373 --> 03:22.108
I was gonna turn you
into a cowboy.

03:22.176 --> 03:23.342
I guess I should've figured
you were more

03:23.410 --> 03:25.211
of a motorcycle helmet
kind of guy.

03:25.279 --> 03:26.846
(Mimics Caleb)
Yes, I am.

03:26.914 --> 03:28.715
Both:
(Laugh)

03:28.783 --> 03:30.382
Hey, if I'm moving
into Caleb's trailer,

03:30.450 --> 03:31.717
I gotta talk the talk,
right?

03:31.785 --> 03:33.285
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

03:33.352 --> 03:35.387
Just practicing.

03:35.455 --> 03:37.389
Hey, can you gimme a hand
with this stuff?

03:37.457 --> 03:39.858
- Yeah, sure.
- Thank you.

03:42.862 --> 03:44.630
Ty:
All right...

03:44.698 --> 03:46.931
Ty: You got it?
Amy: Yeah.

03:54.406 --> 03:55.807
(Engine rumbles)

04:00.946 --> 04:02.579
So...

04:02.647 --> 04:03.914
You never call,
you never write,

04:03.982 --> 04:05.616
and suddenly, you're here?

04:05.683 --> 04:06.717
Good ol' Tim.

04:06.784 --> 04:09.385
No kiss, no hug,
not even a hello.

04:09.453 --> 04:10.420
It's good to see you.

04:10.488 --> 04:11.955
Good to see you too.

04:12.023 --> 04:14.691
But I gotta ask you,
what happened to California?

04:14.759 --> 04:17.494
Well,
California was great--

04:17.560 --> 04:20.262
plenty of work,
tons of money--

04:20.329 --> 04:22.732
but after leaving here,

04:22.799 --> 04:24.100
I just couldn't help feeling

04:24.167 --> 04:26.636
like there was something
missing from my life.

04:26.703 --> 04:28.604
Yeah,
I know the feeling.

04:28.672 --> 04:31.073
And then,
I met Cisco here.

04:32.009 --> 04:32.942
He's a two-year-old,

04:33.010 --> 04:35.710
16 hands
and still growing.

04:38.514 --> 04:39.748
So what, you...

04:39.815 --> 04:40.949
You drove
all the way up here

04:41.017 --> 04:42.083
to show me a horse
you bought?

04:42.151 --> 04:43.484
Oh, I didn't buy the horse,
Tim.

04:43.552 --> 04:44.886
You did.

04:44.954 --> 04:46.420
At least, that's what it says
on the bill of sale.

04:46.488 --> 04:47.588
No, wait a second.

04:47.657 --> 04:48.957
You're giving me
a racehorse?!

04:49.025 --> 04:50.624
Wow, Tim.
The way you picked up on that?

04:50.692 --> 04:51.659
(Inhales tightly)

04:51.726 --> 04:52.993
If he's half as fast as you,

04:53.061 --> 04:55.996
we're gonna have a real winner
on our hands.

04:56.064 --> 04:58.198
<i>Ty:</i> <i>Well, I guess</i>
<i>this about does it.</i>

04:58.266 --> 04:59.667
Yeah.

04:59.734 --> 05:01.401
Are you sure you don't want me
to come with you

05:01.469 --> 05:03.771
and help you settle in?

05:03.838 --> 05:06.605
Thanks, but I don't have
that much stuff, Amy.

05:06.674 --> 05:08.941
Look, I don't wanna make
a big deal about this, okay?

05:09.009 --> 05:10.242
Yeah. No, I know,
you're right.

05:10.310 --> 05:11.343
Just a change of scenery.

05:11.411 --> 05:13.279
Yeah.

05:13.346 --> 05:15.048
- Okay.
- Okay?

05:15.115 --> 05:16.248
Yeah. Bye.

05:16.316 --> 05:19.052
(Hats clunk,
Amy chuckles)

05:19.119 --> 05:20.186
My bad.

05:24.557 --> 05:26.658
You know, maybe I should
just hang onto this,

05:26.726 --> 05:29.094
give you something
to come back for.

05:29.162 --> 05:31.096
I already have plenty
to come back for.

05:34.567 --> 05:36.034
Thanks, Mallory.

05:38.603 --> 05:40.037
Okay. Go on.

05:40.105 --> 05:41.172
See ya.

05:44.242 --> 05:46.711
(Engine sputters
and rumbles)

05:48.213 --> 05:49.780
(Horn beeps twice)

05:51.249 --> 05:52.616
<i>Mallory:</i>
<i>You're right.</i>

05:52.684 --> 05:55.018
You should've kept
the hat.

05:55.086 --> 05:58.621
At least then
you'd have a souvenir.

05:58.689 --> 06:00.023
Mallory...

